<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#9FA6C4"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000" FACE="Verdana">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">kurt</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">If your not looking for a career in smithing would it be worth you while sharping an occasional weapon?  Is it safe or can you lose the weapon your trying to sharpen?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Tlaanya</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">No, when you sharpen a rusty weapon, there is no chance of failure as long as you put in an acceptable weapon and number of stones (1).  I don't see the point of just sharpening weapons for fun unless you want to get you smithing skill up or just to be charitable.  It isn't expensive for a stone (3 cp for 1), so if you wanna be nice, go for it, but don't try and make people pay for sharpening, cause almost no one will.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Sinfulbliss</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Wrong!<BR>You absolutley CAN loose yer weapon.<BR>The only thing that sharpening a weapon does, besides increasing smithing skill, is reduce the delay by a very small amount, usually 1. It may increase the price a little but I'm not sure about that.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Gwaihir</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Sharpening does not increase the value. I have **never** lost something sharpening. The worst is a create an alternate item (which is the unaffected weapon) and I lose the stone (3cp big deal). You will lose a tarnished weapon if you put it in with a sharpening stone, though. <BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Bard Valmi (Tunare)</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">The Halberd cannot be sharpened, and is auto-destroyed. I've never lost anything else due to sharpening failure, and my WIS is only 60.<BR>Smithing (34).</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Minani</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">A patch about 3 months after the release of the game made it so you didn't lose the weapon after failing to sharpen rusty weapons. Prior to that, you lost the weapon when you failed. Now, you just get the weapon back.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</FONT>
